{
  "chunks": [
    {
      "doc_id": "reg_confined_spaces.md",
      "title": "Reg Confined Spaces",
      "content": "# PROTOTYPE SAFETY KNOWLEDGE \u2014 NOT AUTHORITATIVE REGULATORY TEXT.\n# Industrial Safety Standards: Confined Space Management\nDocument ID: REG-CSF-12\nVersion: 1.0\nSource: SafeMesh AI Safety Committee",
      "chunk_index": 0
    },
    {
      "doc_id": "reg_confined_spaces.md",
      "title": "Reg Confined Spaces",
      "content": "## 1. Scope\nThese rules apply to all plant areas classified as Confined Spaces, including storage tanks, boiler drums, and pits.",
      "chunk_index": 1
    },
    {
      "doc_id": "reg_confined_spaces.md",
      "title": "Reg Confined Spaces",
      "content": "## 2. Atmospheric Entry Standards\n- No entry is permitted without an active Confined Space Entry Permit.\n- **Oxygen Levels**: Must remain between 19.5% and 23.5%. Entry is prohibited if oxygen levels drop below 19.5%.\n- **Toxic Gases**: H2S must remain below 10 ppm. CO must remain below 35 ppm.\n- **Continuous Monitoring**: An active watcher must stand outside the space, equipped with continuous remote gas readout.",
      "chunk_index": 2
    },
    {
      "doc_id": "sop_coke_oven.md",
      "title": "Sop Coke Oven",
      "content": "# PROTOTYPE SAFETY KNOWLEDGE \u2014 NOT AUTHORITATIVE REGULATORY TEXT.\n# Standard Operating Procedure (SOP): Coke Oven Operations & Gas Extraction\nDocument ID: SOP-COB-01\nVersion: 4.2\nLast Revised: January 15, 2026",
      "chunk_index": 0
    },
    {
      "doc_id": "sop_coke_oven.md",
      "title": "Sop Coke Oven",
      "content": "## 1. Overview\nThe Coke Oven Battery (COB) produces high-temperature fuel coke by heating coal in the absence of oxygen. This process releases highly volatile and combustible coke oven gas. Safe extraction of this gas requires continuous mechanical ventilation and atmospheric monitoring.",
      "chunk_index": 1
    },
    {
      "doc_id": "sop_coke_oven.md",
      "title": "Sop Coke Oven",
      "content": "## 2. Threshold Safety Controls\n1. **Combustible Gas Levels (LEL)**:\n   - Warning alert at 20% LEL.\n   - Critical evacuation alert at 40% LEL.\n2. **Ventilation Performance**:\n   - Extraction fans must operate above 75% flow efficiency at all times.\n   - Efficiency below 70% requires immediate operator dispatch.\n   - Efficiency below 50% requires suspension of all active Hot Work permits in the zone.",
      "chunk_index": 2
    },
    {
      "doc_id": "sop_coke_oven.md",
      "title": "Sop Coke Oven",
      "content": "## 3. Simultaneous Operations (SIMOPS)\n- Hot Work (welding, cutting, grinding) is strictly prohibited in the Coke Oven Battery if ventilation efficiency drops below 70% OR combustible gas is detected above 15% LEL.\n- If ventilation efficiency drops below 50%, the control room operator must initiate an emergency permit suspension and safety hold on all active operations within the zone.",
      "chunk_index": 3
    }
  ],
